{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:04:59.645Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Envisioning Interactive Design**\n\nI've confirmed the codebase utilizes `motion/react`, opening the door for dynamic, modern page animations. My focus shifts to designing a highly interactive page, leveraging the framework's capabilities. The goal is to create a fluid, expensive feel!\n\n\n**Designing Admin Dashboard Layout**\n\nI'm now detailing the Admin Governance workspace. It'll be structured around sections like a header with title, description, and badge, plus a prominent top stats grid with hover effects and status bars for key metrics. The grid will contain cards such as \"Critical Alerts Velocity\", \"Global Compliance Rating\", \"Hardware Key Sealing\", and \"Active Enclave Guards\".\n\n\n**Detailing eBPF Metrics**\n\nI'm currently integrating eBPF tracing data, specifically node counts, into the dashboard. A small status ticker or sparkline visualization for the `Kernel-level eBPF Tracing` value is being considered to provide a quick visual overview. The goal is to make the dashboard informative and dynamic.\n\n\n**Visualizing Security Telemetry**\n\nI'm now integrating a sovereign topology map as a key element. This interactive SVG graphic will visually represent security telemetry flow. Users can interact with the graphic, hovering over nodes to reveal detailed telemetry status and key metrics, as well as have click functionality!\n\n\n**Crafting Incident Resolution**\n\nI'm now designing an incident resolution workspace within the admin panel. This includes a glass backdrop and detailed metadata display for selected alerts. I'm also planning for a real-time log stream terminal and an actionable resolution form. The form will handle officer assignment, status setting, note-taking, and policy overrides with immediate feedback, using a custom toast notification.\n\n\n"}}
