{"ts":"2026-06-27T08:13:47.425Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Dividing the Content**\n\nMy Right Side content block is quite large, at 11,241 characters. I've decided to split it. Part R1 will be the Enclave Topology Map, visualized as a `WorkspaceCard` with SVG and client nodes. Part R2 will be the Telemetry Inspector, implemented using `AnimatePresence` with `selectedAlert`.\n\n\n**Refining R1 Implementation**\n\nI'm making excellent progress on splitting the Right Side content block. I've replaced the placeholder with the new Topology Map (R1) component, utilizing `WorkspaceCard` and an SVG visualization of the enclave topology. I've focused on styling and ensuring a clear visual hierarchy with headers and visual cues. The grid and layout are perfect, and now I'm working on animating the client nodes to demonstrate their movement.\n\n\n**Visualizing Node Connections**\n\nI've been working on visualizing the connections within the topology map. I've added SVG paths to illustrate the relationships between nodes, using dashed lines for less significant connections and solid lines for critical ones. The central hub is now highlighted with an animated glow, making it stand out as the focal point. I'm focusing on clarity through visual cues.\n\n\n**Refining Node Interactions**\n\nI'm now implementing interactive elements within the topology map. I've added click handlers to the nodes. Clicking on \"ADMIN\" triggers a toast notification about TLS 1.3 security. Clicking on \"APEX-SEC\" now filters the view and displays an informative toast as well. I'm focusing on providing users with immediate feedback and functionality.\n\n\n**Adding Client Filters**\n\nI've just added filtering capabilities to the topology map, allowing users to select specific client enclaves. I implemented click handlers on the client nodes. Clicking \"MED-CLINIC\" filters to \"National Health Enclave\" and shows a toast. Similarly, \"RETAIL-CORE\" filters to \"Sovereign Retail Group\" with another informative toast. I'm prioritizing user control and intuitive feedback.\n\n\n**Implementing Filter Clearing**\n\nI've just added a feature to clear the client filters, which is displayed beneath the filtered view on the Topology Map. A button, complete with an appropriate icon, allows the user to reset and view all clients. I'm aiming for ease of use by offering clear client filtering controls.\n\n\n"}}
